# Hyperliquid Educational Dashboard - Environment Variables

## Required Environment Variables

### Hyperliquid API Configuration
```env
# Main API endpoint for Hyperliquid
VITE_HYPERLIQUID_API_URL=https://api.hyperliquid.xyz

# WebSocket endpoint for real-time data
VITE_HYPERLIQUID_WS_URL=wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws

# Enable testnet trading (set to 'true' for development)
VITE_ENABLE_TESTNET_TRADING=false
```

### Supabase Configuration (Required)
```env
# Your Supabase project URL
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url

# Supabase anonymous key (safe to expose)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key

# For server-side operations (keep secret)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key
```

### Wallet Integration (Optional)
```env
# WalletConnect project ID (for WalletConnect support)
VITE_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID=your_walletconnect_project_id
```

## Platform-Specific Setup

### Netlify
1. Go to Site settings > Environment variables
2. Add each variable listed above
3. Deploy the site

### Vercel
1. Go to Project settings > Environment Variables
2. Add each variable for all environments (Production, Preview, Development)
3. Redeploy the project

### Local Development
1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env.local`
2. Fill in your actual values
3. Run `npm run dev`

## Security Notes

- All `VITE_*` variables are exposed to the client
- Keep `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` secret and only use in server environments
- Never commit actual environment values to version control
- Use different Supabase projects for development and production

## Testing Configuration

For testing the deployed application:

```env
# Use testnet for safe testing
VITE_ENABLE_TESTNET_TRADING=true
VITE_HYPERLIQUID_API_URL=https://api.hyperliquid-testnet.xyz
VITE_HYPERLIQUID_WS_URL=wss://api.hyperliquid-testnet.xyz/ws
```